{"kind":"article","sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (24 min)","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/224","type":"reference","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-224-Evaluate-your-app-for-Accessibility-Nutrition-Labels","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Related-Sessions","type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions","level":2},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24-10074-Get-started-with-Dynamic-Type"],"type":"links","style":"list"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Accessibility Nutrition Labels on your App Store product page to highlight the accessibility features supported by your app. You’ll learn how to evaluate your app’s accessibility features — such as VoiceOver, Larger Text, Captions, and more — and choose accurate and informative Accessibility Nutrition Labels. You’ll also find out how to approach accessibility throughout the design phase."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-224-evaluate-your-app-for-accessibility-nutrition-labels"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC25","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Evaluate your app for Accessibility Nutrition Labels","role":"sampleCode"},"references":{"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/224":{"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/224","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/224"},"WWDC25.jpg":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25.jpg"}],"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25","abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 26, Swift 6.2, iOS\/macOS\/tvOS\/visionOS 26.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"New APIs: ","type":"text"},{"code":"Foundation Models","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"AlarmKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"PermissionKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and more.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25","type":"topic","kind":"article","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","type":"card"}],"role":"collectionGroup","title":"WWDC25"},"WWDC25-Icon.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Learn More…","type":"text"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC24-10074-Get-started-with-Dynamic-Type":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc24-10074-get-started-with-dynamic-type","type":"topic","title":"Get started with Dynamic Type","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24-10074-Get-started-with-Dynamic-Type","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Dynamic Type lets people choose their preferred text size across the system and all of their apps. To help you get started supporting Dynamic Type, we’ll cover the fundamentals: How it works, how to find issues with scaling text in your app, and how to take practical steps using SwiftUI and UIKit to create a great Dynamic Type experience. We’ll also show how you can best use the Large Content Viewer to make navigation controls accessible to everyone."}]}}}